<H3> <TI>   Controversy Over Tax Reform Proposal Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Stimulus Package Meeting Postponed </H4>
<F P=102> OW0302114294 Tokyo KYODO in English 1135 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0302114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 3 KYODO -- The Economic Planning Agency 
said Thursday [3 February] it decided not to hold an economic 
ministers' meeting to decide on the government's fresh 
pump-priming package during the day. The adoption of the 
stimulative package, originally scheduled for Thursday, will be 
put off until Friday or afterward, agency officials said. 

</TEXT>

