<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Vo Van Kiet Interview on Thrift, Corruption </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0202150394 Hanoi VNA in English 1448 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0202150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb. 2 -- It's time to launch a 
nation-wide campaign for practising thrift and fighting public 
property embezzlement, and wastefulness, says Prime Minister Vo 
Van Kiet in a recent interview to VIETNAM NEWS AGENCY. 
  Premier Kiet recalled the Vietnamese people's tradition of 
industry and thrift. He stressed that to practise thrift and 
fight against public property embezzlement and wastefulness have 
become ever more urgent in Vietnam, a poor country which is 
fighting against the danger of lagging behind others in the 
region, and which needs economic accumulation for its own 
industrialization and modernization. 
  The prime minister said he himself and many others worried 
about the situation such as capital construction whose wasteful 
expenditures and losses accounted for at least 10-20 per cent of 
its capital. He called for stepping up the on-going nationwide 
a campaign for practising economy and fight against public 
property embezzlement. 
  He also recalled the government's responsibility in working 
out, and guiding the implementation of policies encouraging 
thrift practice and embezzlement prevention. The authorities at 
all levels should work out concrete and practical plans of 
action for thrift practice and embezzlement prevention in state 
institutions, enterprises and in society as a whole, the prime 
minister stressed. 

</TEXT>

