<H3> <TI>   Canberra Condemns Attack on Citizen in Algeria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0202063894 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 2 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0202063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Australian Government says it condemns in the 
strongest possible terms an attack in Algeria in which a 
Frenchman was killed and an Australian injured. French 
cameraman (Olivier Kenana), age 34, died in the incident and his 
Australian collegue (Jeff Allan White), age 35, was shot in the 
back of the head. He is in a serious condition in a hospital. 
  Algerian officials said the two men were attacked by 
suspected Muslim fundamentalists while filming in the Kazbah 
district of the capital, Algiers. [They were] there are on an 
assignment for the American broadcasting company. The foreign 
affairs department said Australia has diplomatic representation 
in Algeria but a British diplomat will visit Mr. (White) 
tomorrow. The French Government has also condemned the attack. 

