<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Confirms Diplomatic Visit Itinerary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0302120394 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 3 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0302120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 2 February, the government confirmed its 
diplomatic itinerary, according to which Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa will visit the PRC on 19-21 March and Foreign Minister 
Tsutomu Hata will visit Russia on 19-20 March. It has started 
working out the details of the planned visits with the 
governments of the respective nations. 
  A while ago, Prime Minister Hosokawa frankly stated that the 
pre-World War II Japanese invasion of Asian countries "was a war 
of aggression." China, which highly acclaimed the prime 
minister's remarks, has requested he visit the country soon. 
However, political uncertainties in Japan have delayed 
coordinating the schedule. 

</TEXT>

