<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Space Agency Successfully Launches H-2 Rocket </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0302225694 Tokyo KYODO in English 2240 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0302225694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tanegashima, Kagoshima Pref., Feb. 4 KYODO -- 
Japan's Space Agency on Friday [4 February] launched the 
country's first fully domestically developed rocket from its 
space center in southern Japan. 
  The H-2 series rocket lifted off from the National Space 
Development Agency's Tanegashima Space Center at 7:20 A.M. [2220 
GMT]. 
  The launching had originally been set for Tuesday but was 
postponed until Friday because of bad weather and a faulty air 
duct that came loose. 

</TEXT>

