<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary on U.S. Trade Representative Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Objective Criteria Request Viewed </H4>
<F P=102> OW0402113894 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 4 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 7 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0402113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Trade Representative Kantor, on a visit to 
Japan, met with Prime Minister Hosokawa at the latter's official 
residence on the afternoon of 3 February. Commenting on a 
6-trillion-yen income tax cut and the "creation of a national 
welfare tax" that the prime minister announced in the early dawn 
of 3 February, Mr. Kantor said: "You made a proper decision." 
In this way, he highly rated the prime minister's tax measures 
taken as part of stimulus measures. 
  Mr. Kantor met with Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii prior to 
his meeting with the prime minister. During the meeting, Mr. 
Kantor warned that "if the Japan-U.S. summit slated for 11 
February ends in failure, it would have a great impact on the 
world economy." Referring to negotiations on the insurance 
sector under the Japan- U.S. economic framework talks, Mr. 
Kantor asked that Japan adopt "objective criteria" to measure 
the share of foreign insurance firms on the Japanese insurance 
market. In response, Finance Minister Fujii said: "The share 
is something that must be decided by the business activities of 
foreign firms." 

</TEXT>

