<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Little Impact' of U.S. Monetary Policy Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0702125294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 6 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0702125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A senior official of the Bank of Japan, in 
connection with U.S. decision on 4 February to implement a 
tighter monetary policy, believes that "it is a precautionary 
measure against inflation and will have little impact on 
Japanese economy, since chances are slim that long- and 
short-term interest rates in the United States will rise 
rapidly." He, therefore, maintains that "Japanese monetary 
policies will not be affected." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

