<H3> <TI>   Tokyo-Moscow Defense Meeting Ends 4 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0502124994 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Feb 93 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0502124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Japan-Russia meeting on defense policy and 
planning, which was held at the Foreign Ministry for two days, 
ended on 4 February. It was attended by officials in charge of 
defense and foreign policy affairs from the two countries. 
  At the meeting, the Japanese side pointed out that Russian 
forces in the Far East have become an unstable factor to the 
security of northeast Asian nations. In response, the Russian 
side stressed that Russia has continued its effort to promote 
disarmament and reduce its forces. At the meeting, the Russian 
side said that Russia hopes to join the Asia Pacific Economic 
Cooperation (APEC) forum. 
  Shunji Yanai, director general of the Foreign Policy Bureau 
in the Foreign Ministry, attended the meeting and Agayev, chief 
of the Analysis and Estimate Department in the Russian Foreign 
Ministry, and other Russian officials attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

