<H3> <TI>   Operating Outlays To Rise in MOF 1994 Budget </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0702021294 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 7 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0702021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 7 February Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] The outline of the Ministry of Finance [MOF] draft 
budget for fiscal year 1994 has been set, except for the 
unresolved dispute on the income tax cut and the national 
welfare tax. 
  The rate of increase for general operating expenditures will 
be 2.4 percent, compared to the original budget for fiscal 1993, 
representing the lowest growth rate in six years. However, all 
requests for allocations for public work projects were approved, 
showing consideration for the sluggish economy. 
  In terms of taxation, the expansion of preferential 
treatment 
for land replacement, and the strengthening of taxation on 
corporate unaccounted expenditures and entertainment expenses 
have been decided upon. However, coordination within the 
government and among the ruling coalition parties on the income 
tax cut and the accompanying tax hike has been delayed until 7 
February, and if a conclusion is not reached, this may seriously 
affect the schedule for the unofficial announcement of the MOF 
draft budget (originally set for 10 February). 

</TEXT>

