<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   French TV Equipment Given as `Token of Cooperation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0702130194 Phnom Penh AKP in English 1002 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0702130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP February 7 -- France has provided TV 
technical equipment worth 2.5 million francs to Cambodia. 
  It was the first time that France provided such equipment to 
Cambodia since the formation of the royal government of 
Cambodia. The gift was handed over in Phnom Penh last Friday, 
4 February, by Parcsel Charlat, French charge d'affaires a.i to 
Cambodia, to Ieng Muli, minister of information. On that 
occasion, Minister Ieng Muli expressed thanks to the government 
of France for its assistance to Cambodia for the development of 
mass media in the country. 
  Parcsel Charlat said in his reply that the gift was the 
contribution to the development of TV broadcasting in Cambodia 
and a token of cooperation between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

